message.content:
You are fixing a bug in `src/Importer/ContactImporter.php`.

## Issue

The current pagination loop has an infinite loop risk: when all remaining pages are already downloaded (skip via `continue`), the `$hasNext` variable is never updated (it retains its value from the previous non-skipped iteration). This causes the loop to keep advancing `$offset` indefinitely.

## Fix

Rewrite the `import()` method with a cleaner loop that handles the skip case properly:

```php
public function import(): void
{
    $offset = 0;

    while (true) {
        if ($this->pageTracker->isDownloaded($offset, $this->pageSize)) {
            echo "Skipping offset={$offset} (already downloaded)\n";
            $offset += $this->pageSize;
            // If we've skipped too many pages without finding new data, stop.
            // We rely on the API having a finite number of pages.
            // After 10 consecutive skipped pages beyond any known next link, stop.
            // Better: just continue — the next non-skipped page will set hasNext.
            continue;
        }

        $response = $this->apiClient->getContacts($offset, $this->pageSize);
        $contacts = $response['data'];

        if (empty($contacts)) {
            break;
        }

        foreach ($contacts as $contact) {
            $row = $this->mapper->mapToRow($contact);
            $this->contactRepository->upsert($row);
        }

        $this->pageTracker->markDownloaded($offset, $this->pageSize, count($contacts));
        echo "Imported offset={$offset}: " . count($contacts) . " contacts\n";

        $offset += $this->pageSize;

        if (!isset($response['links']['next'])) {
            break;
        }
    }
}
```

Wait — this still has the issue that if all pages are downloaded, we loop forever via `continue`. 

The real fix is: track a "consecutive skips" counter, and if we skip too many pages in a row without hitting the API, stop. OR better: when we skip a page, we still need to know if there's a next page. 

The cleanest solution is to check against the pages table to know when we've passed the last known offset:

```php
public function import(): void
{
    $offset = 0;
    $consecutiveSkips = 0;
    $maxConsecutiveSkips = 10; // Stop after 10 pages of all-skipped

    while (true) {
        if ($this->pageTracker->isDownloaded($offset, $this->pageSize)) {
            echo "Skipping offset={$offset} (already downloaded)\n";
            $offset += $this->pageSize;
            $consecutiveSkips++;

            if ($consecutiveSkips >= $maxConsecutiveSkips) {
                echo "Stopping: {$maxConsecutiveSkips} consecutive pages already downloaded.\n";
                break;
            }
            continue;
        }

        $consecutiveSkips = 0;
        $response = $this->apiClient->getContacts($offset, $this->pageSize);
        $contacts = $response['data'];

        if (empty($contacts)) {
            break;
        }

        foreach ($contacts as $contact) {
            $row = $this->mapper->mapToRow($contact);
            $this->contactRepository->upsert($row);
        }

        $this->pageTracker->markDownloaded($offset, $this->pageSize, count($contacts));
        echo "Imported offset={$offset}: " . count($contacts) . " contacts\n";

        $offset += $this->pageSize;

        if (!isset($response['links']['next'])) {
            break;
        }
    }
}
```

## Your Job

1. Read the current `src/Importer/ContactImporter.php`
2. Replace the `import()` method with the fixed version above
3. Run `vendor/bin/phpunit` to verify existing tests still pass (there may be no tests for this class — just check the full test suite passes)
4. Commit:
```bash
git add src/Importer/ContactImporter.php
git commit -m "fix: prevent infinite loop in ContactImporter when all pages already downloaded"
```
5. Report back

